data.title: Domino’s Pizza’s stock price grew faster than Amazon’s, Apple’s or Google’s under its departing CEO
data.meta_description: When Patrick Doyle took over as CEO of Domino’s Pizza in 2010, the massive pizza chain was basically in shambles. Eight years later, Doyle is stepping down after presiding over one of the most impressive turnaround stories in modern business history.
